<body><main class="wrap">{% endblock %}{% block body %}<nav class="langsw" aria-label="Language / Idioma"><a href="/research/llm-cost-calculator" hreflang="en" aria-current="page">EN</a> · <a href="/es/research/llm-cost-calculator" hreflang="es">ES</a> · <a href="/ja/research/llm-cost-calculator" hreflang="ja">JA</a></nav><h1>LLM Cost Calculator</h1>
<p>Estimate your monthly LLM spend across popular models. Enter your usage pattern below and see costs compared side-by-side. All prices are per-million-tokens as of July 2026.</p>

<h2>Pre-calculated costs by usage tier</h2>
<p>Here's what each usage tier costs per month across popular models, based on typical request patterns:</p>
<table>
<thead><tr><th>Model</th><th>Light (1K req/mo)</th><th>Medium (10K req/mo)</th><th>Heavy (100K req/mo)</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>GPT-4o</td><td>$3.25</td><td>$32.50</td><td>$325.00</td></tr>
<tr><td>GPT-5</td><td>$12.50</td><td>$125.00</td><td>$1,250.00</td></tr>
<tr><td>GPT-5 mini</td><td>$1.95</td><td>$19.50</td><td>$195.00</td></tr>
<tr><td>Claude Sonnet 4</td><td>$4.50</td><td>$45.00</td><td>$450.00</td></tr>
<tr><td>Claude Opus 4</td><td>$22.50</td><td>$225.00</td><td>$2,250.00</td></tr>
<tr><td>Gemini 2.5 Pro</td><td>$1.75</td><td>$17.50</td><td>$175.00</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="https://platform.xiaomimimo.com?ref=LHT8UJ">MiMO</a></td><td>$1.20</td><td>$12.00</td><td>$120.00</td></tr>
<tr><td>DeepSeek R1</td><td>$0.80</td><td>$8.00</td><td>$80.00</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><em>Light:</em> 1K requests/mo, 500 input + 200 output tokens. <em>Medium:</em> 10K requests/mo, 1,000 input + 500 output tokens. <em>Heavy:</em> 100K requests/mo, 2,000 input + 1,000 output tokens.</p>

<h2>Interactive calculator</h2>
<div class="calc">
<label for="model">Model</label>
<select id="model">
<option value="gpt4o">GPT-4o ($2.50 / $10.00)</option>
<option value="gpt5">GPT-5 ($10.00 / $30.00)</option>
<option value="gpt5mini">GPT-5 mini ($1.50 / $6.00)</option>
<option value="claude_sonnet">Claude Sonnet 4 ($3.00 / $15.00)</option>
<option value="claude_opus">Claude Opus 4 ($15.00 / $75.00)</option>
<option value="gemini_pro">Gemini 2.5 Pro ($1.25 / $10.00)</option>
<option value="mimo">MiMO ($0.80 / $3.20)</option>
<option value="deepseek">DeepSeek R1 ($0.55 / $2.19)</option>
</select>
<label for="requests">Requests per month</label>
<input type="number" id="requests" value="10000" min="1" step="1000" />
<label for="inputTokens">Avg input tokens per request</label>
<input type="number" id="inputTokens" value="1000" min="1" step="100" />
<label for="outputTokens">Avg output tokens per request</label>
<input type="number" id="outputTokens" value="500" min="1" step="100" />
<button onclick="calculate()">Calculate cost</button>
<div id="results"></div>
</div>

<script>
var models={gpt4o:{name:"GPT-4o",input:2.50,output:10.00},gpt5:{name:"GPT-5",input:10.00,output:30.00},gpt5mini:{name:"GPT-5 mini",input:1.50,output:6.00},claude_sonnet:{name:"Claude Sonnet 4",input:3.00,output:15.00},claude_opus:{name:"Claude Opus 4",input:15.00,output:75.00},gemini_pro:{name:"Gemini 2.5 Pro",input:1.25,output:10.00},mimo:{name:"MiMO",input:0.80,output:3.20},deepseek:{name:"DeepSeek R1",input:0.55,output:2.19}};
function calculate(){
var m=models[document.getElementById("model").value];
var r=parseInt(document.getElementById("requests").value)||0;
var it=parseInt(document.getElementById("inputTokens").value)||0;
var ot=parseInt(document.getElementById("outputTokens").value)||0;
var inputCost=(r*it/1000000)*m.input;
var outputCost=(r*ot/1000000)*m.output;
var total=inputCost+outputCost;
var html='<table><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead><tbody>';
html+='<tr><td>Model</td><td>'+m.name+'</td></tr>';
html+='<tr><td>Total requests/mo</td><td>'+r.toLocaleString()+'</td></tr>';
html+='<tr><td>Input cost/mo</td><td>$'+inputCost.toFixed(2)+'</td></tr>';
html+='<tr><td>Output cost/mo</td><td>$'+outputCost.toFixed(2)+'</td></tr>';
html+='<tr><td><strong>Total estimated cost/mo</strong></td><td><strong>$'+total.toFixed(2)+'</strong></td></tr>';
html+='<tr><td>Cost per request</td><td>$'+(total/r).toFixed(5)+'</td></tr>';
html+='</tbody></table>';
html+='<p style="font-size:.85rem;color:#647289">Estimate only. Does not include cache discounts, batch API pricing, or reasoning token overhead. Actual costs vary by provider billing practices.</p>';
document.getElementById("results").innerHTML=html;
}
</script>

<h2>How to use this calculator</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong>Pick your model</strong> from the dropdown. Prices reflect standard API rates as of July 2026.</li>
<li><strong>Enter your request volume</strong> — how many API calls you make per month.</li>
<li><strong>Estimate token counts</strong> — the average number of input and output tokens per request. If you're unsure, start with 1,000 input / 500 output for chat, or 3,000 input / 1,000 output for code generation.</li>
<li><strong>Hit Calculate</strong> to see your estimated monthly cost split by input and output.</li>
</ol>

<h2>How to reduce your estimate</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Use prompt caching.</strong> If your prompts have a stable prefix, cached reads can cut input costs by 50–90%. See <a href="/research/prompt-caching-explained">prompt caching explained</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Switch models by task.</strong> Route simple queries to cheaper models and reserve expensive ones for complex tasks. This is <a href="/research/model-routing">model routing</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Use batch APIs.</strong> Non-urgent workloads can use batch pricing at 50% off.</li>
<li><strong>Try cheaper providers.</strong> <a href="https://platform.xiaomimimo.com?ref=LHT8UJ">MiMO</a> and DeepSeek offer significantly lower rates for comparable quality on many tasks.</li>
</ul>

